using LinearAlgebra
function scalar_product(x, y)
    dot(x, y)
end

function mul_vector_matrix(x, y)
    x * y
end

scalar_product([1;2;3],[4;2;1])

Sprawdzenie czasu działania funkcji dla przykładowych wartości¶

In [2]:
using Random
using LinearAlgebra

function test_scalars()
    times = Float32[]
    for i = 1:200
        for j = 1:10
             push!(times, @elapsed dot(rand(1:100, i), rand(1:100,i)))
        end
        sleep(0.001)
    end
    times
end

function test_matrixes()
    times = Float32[]
    for i = 1:200
        for j = 1:10
            push!(times, @elapsed (rand(1:100, i,i)*rand(1:100,i)))
        end
        sleep(0.001)
    end
    times
end

function vector_sizes()
    array = Int[]
    for i = 1:200
        for j = 1:10
        push!(array, i)
        end
    end
    array
end
Out[2]:
vector_sizes (generic function with 1 method)

using Statistics
gd =  groupby(df, :wielkość)
avg_sd_df = combine(gd, :iloczyn_skalarny => mean, :mnozenie_macierzy => mean, :iloczyn_skalarny => std,:mnozenie_macierzy => std)
